definition: to confer/to grant/to bestow a title/to seal/classifier for sealed objects, esp. letters
surname Yin/abbr. for 印度[Yin4 du4]
to print/to mark/to engrave/a seal/a print/a stamp/a mark/a trace/image

sentences.english: The frozen Dark Jedi lured Aayla to his tomb, and had her deactivate the stasis shield.
sentences.chinese: 被冰冻的黑暗绝地引诱她进入坟墓，打开了封印罩。

sentences.english: On the throne sits God who has a book with seven seals.
sentences.chinese: 上帝坐在宝座上，拿着一本有七个封印的书。
所有货物都加盖了检验合格封印。

sentences.english: They then leave, sealing the sanctuary ahead of the pharaoh's daily visit.
sentences.chinese: 他们拜别的时候，封印在法老每天的到临前再次封闭。

sentences.english: The rage and agonies of the people. Those who were confined here. With.
sentences.chinese: 那股被封印在此之人的痛苦与愤怒。

sentences.english: You sealed your demise when you took what was mine.
sentences.chinese: 当你拿走属于我的东西时，你封印了你的死亡。

sentences.english: The ancient seal will be broken, awakening nightmares of ages past.
sentences.chinese: 那古代的封印会被毁坏，唤醒遥远过去的恶梦。

sentences.english: Inuyasha and is discovered to be the reincarnation of Kikyo.
sentences.chinese: 在那里，她解除了犬夜叉的封印，并发现是桔梗转世。

sentences.english: No wonder the late king had sealed it away.
sentences.chinese: 没想到父王把它封印在这里。

sentences.english: No visible corrosion on the piston and bore of cylinder where contact with seal.
sentences.chinese: 没有可看见的联络以封印圆筒的腐蚀在活塞和打扰。

sentences.english: The Seal Lock is now available in the Cash Shop.
sentences.chinese: 封印锁现在在购物商城有售。

sentences.english: There she unseals Inuyasha and is discovered to be the reincarnation of Kikyo.
sentences.chinese: 在那里，她解除了犬夜叉的封印，并发现是桔梗转世。

sentences.english: Wings sealed in day, began to fly in twilight.
sentences.chinese: 双翼被白日所封印，在暮色中渐渐展开。

occult force/the power of a God or spirit
